                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Karnataka phone ban
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bangalore, Feb. 5: The Karnataka government has issued circulars asking schools to prohibit teachers from using cellphones on campus.         
	The government had received complaints from parents that the mobile phones were causing disturbances in classrooms, minister for primary and secondary education Vishveshwara Hegde Kageri said. It (usage of the cellphones) is disturbing academic activities and discipline at schools.         
	Only principals and headmasters may be allowed to use cellphones in their offices for administrative purposes, he added.                                                                                                                                                           
